0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__articlePage","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Pergola vs. Gazebo: Finding Your Perfect Fit\",\"image\":[\"https://www.ldndecks.com/images/img15.jpeg\"],\"datePublished\":\"2026-03-15T04:00:00.000Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-03-15T04:00:00.000Z\",\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks Team\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\"}],\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/ldndecks-logo.webp\"}},\"description\":\"Looking to add definition and shade to your stone patio? We break down the structural differences between open-air pergolas and enclosed-roof gazebos.\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/blog/pergola-vs-gazebo\"},\"isAccessibleForFree\":true,\"inLanguage\":\"en-US\",\"speakable\":{\"@type\":\"SpeakableSpecification\",\"cssSelector\":[\".leadParagraph\",\"h1\",\"h2\"]}}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgWrapper","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"src":"/images/img15.jpeg","alt":"Pergola vs. Gazebo: Finding Your Perfect Fit","fill":true,"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroImg","priority":true,"sizes":"100vw"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgOverlay","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerLarge","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__backLink","children":"← Back to News"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__title","children":"Pergola vs. Gazebo: Finding Your Perfect Fit"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__author","children":["By ","Loudoun Decks Team"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__divider","children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"March 15, 2026"}]]}]]}]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerNarrow","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentBody","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__leadParagraph","children":"Looking to add definition and shade to your stone patio? We break down the structural differences between open-air pergolas and enclosed-roof gazebos."}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"When looking to add vertical architecture, shade, and definition to an exposed patio or backyard space, the choice often comes down to a pergola or a gazebo. Understanding the subtle but distinct structural differences between these two features ensures you select the right fit for your property."}],["$","h2","1",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"The Open-Air Elegance of a Pergola"}],["$","p","2",{"children":"A pergola features a slatted or lattice open-roof system supported by large columns or posts. It doesn’t provide complete shelter from the rain, but its primary purpose is to diffuse harsh sunlight and provide a gorgeous architectural framework for climbing vines, hanging wisteria, and string lights."}],["$","h3","3",{"style":{"marginTop":"30px","marginBottom":"15px","color":"#222"},"children":"When to Choose a Pergola"}],["$","p","4",{"children":"- You want partial shade without blocking out the sky completely.\n- You are looking for a structural feature to anchor an outdoor kitchen or dining table.\n- You want a lighter, more breezy architectural footprint."}],"$L4","$L5","$L6","$L7","$L8"],"$L9"]}]}]}],"$La"]}],["$Lb"],"$Lc"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"Jebrcr4Vyd2YosxlccnHN"}
4:["$","h2","5",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"The Complete Protection of a Gazebo"}]
5:["$","p","6",{"children":"A gazebo, on the other hand, is a geometrically enclosed structure with a fully closed, pitched roof (often shingled) and usually a built-in elevated floor. It offers complete protection from rain, snow, and extreme sun exposure."}]
6:["$","h3","7",{"style":{"marginTop":"30px","marginBottom":"15px","color":"#222"},"children":"When to Choose a Gazebo"}]
7:["$","p","8",{"children":"- You want a dry, sheltered retreat even during summer thunderstorms.\n- You prefer a heavier, more permanent structural look that matches your home’s roofline.\n- You intend to fully screen the walls to prevent insect intrusion."}]
8:["$","p","9",{"children":"Ultimately, if you want an elegant, airy garden feel, choose the pergola. If you want a dry, highly protected outdoor room, the gazebo is the undeniable winner."}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__conclusionBox","children":[["$","h3",null,{"children":"Ready to upgrade your outdoor living space?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Contact Loudoun Decks today for a free estimate and planning consultation."}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/contact","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__ctaBtn","children":"Get Started"}]]}]
